{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RatSvGz5oQRD8AYZqdQZBG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error keeps happening: `unable to find real backend for alternative backend demo-canary-echo-80. Deleting.`\n\nAnd there was NO reload after the canary ingress was processed (after the second reload for canary-stable). Let me look at this from a different angle.\n\nLet me check the nginx controller version to understand the behavior:\n- The controller says it's looking for `demo-canary-echo-80`\n- The canary ingress routes to `canary-echo` service on port 80\n- The service `canary-echo` exists with endpoint `10.244.0.92:5678`\n- The canary-echo service maps port 80 to pod port 5678, and the endpoint is registered at the pod port\n\nThe controller is deleting the canary backend, which suggests it can't find the matching backend. Let me trace through the nginx ingress configuration to see what's happening.\n\nLooking at the two ingresses, canary-stable has paths for `/health` and `/`, while canary-canary also has `/`. When the controller processes a canary ingress, it needs to find a corresponding \"real\" (non-canary) ingress for the same hostname to use as the primary backend. The warning about not finding the real backend for the alternative backend suggests the controller can't establish this relationship. I need to dig into the nginx-ingress source code to find where this validation error is coming from, and check what version is actually running in this environment.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1286,"cache_read_input_tokens":50136,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1286},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ae239c15-9c85