{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ETB1HeVo8x8ML8xQH7cxTg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture!\n\nLooking at the nginx config:\n\nLine 337: `server_name canary.example.com ;`\nLine 350: `location / {`\nLine 356: `set $location_path \"/\";`\nLine 373: `set $proxy_upstream_name \"upstream-default-backend\";`\n\nThe `canary.example.com` server block only has one location: `location /` with `$proxy_upstream_name \"upstream-default-backend\"`.\n\nLine 452: `server_name demo.example.com ;`  \nLine 465: `location ~* \"^/app\" {` with `$proxy_upstream_name \"demo-demo-app-80\"`\nLine 563: `location ~* \"^/\" {` with `$proxy_upstream_name \"upstream-default-backend\"`\n\nSo the `demo.example.com` server has two location blocks: the more specific `/app` pattern that routes to the demo app, and then a catch-all `^/` pattern that falls back to the default backend.\n\nFor `canary.example.com`, the `location /` is pointing to `upstream-default-backend` instead of the `demo-stable-echo-80` backend that's registered in the Lua API. This is the key issue—the stable backend exists in the backends list, but the nginx config still references the default backend. This suggests the nginx config was reloaded before the stable echo endpoints were actually available or discoverable. The Lua rewrite module runs at request time and can dynamically update `$proxy_upstream_name`, but the access logs are showing `[upstream-default-backend]` instead of the expected `[demo-stable-echo-80]`, which suggests the Lua code isn't actually overriding the static nginx.conf value. Let me look at the access log format to understand what's being logged. The backend was registered dynamically after the reload at 09:02:39, but the test requests I saw were from 09:00:09 and 09:00:25, which happened before that. I need to check if there's been a request since the backend became available, and I'm noticin